y don't crash\n  // 20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n  // [Full test code provided above]\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/TASK.md`\nThe task file specifies:\n\n**Feature**: Full-Text Search for Notes API\n\n**Requirements**:\n1. **Search Endpoint** (`GET /notes/search?q=<query>`): Full-text search using SQLite FTS5, BM25 ranking, snippet highlighting with `<mark>` tags, phrase support, pagination (20 per page), response with `{ results, total, page, perPage }`\n2. **Suggest Endpoint** (`GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`): Returns up to 5 matching titles, response with `{ results }`\n3. **FTS Index Sync**: Keep index in sync on create/update/delete operations\n\n**Existing Files**:\n- `src/db.ts` - Database setup\n- `src/models.ts` - Interfaces (SearchResult, SuggestResult defined)\n- `src/routes.ts` - CRUD routes\n- `src/errors.ts` - Error handling\n- `src/server.ts` - Express setup\n- `src/seed.ts` - ~50 sample notes\n\n**Tests**:\n- 15 CRUD tests (notes.test.ts) - must continue passing\n- 20 search tests (search.test.ts) - must pass after implementation\n\n**Validation**: `npm test` - All 35 tests must pass\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **Current State**: The codebase has a working CRUD API for notes with tag-based filtering, but no full-text search functionality.\n\n2. **What's Missing**: The search endpoints (`/notes/search` and `/notes/search/suggest`) are not implemented in `src/routes.ts`.\n\n3. **Database**: Currently uses a simple `notes` table. FTS5 implementation will need:\n   - FTS5 virtual table creation\n   - Trigger-based or manual synchronization\n   - BM25 ranking support\n\n4. **Dependencies**: All necessary packages are already in place (better-sqlite3, express, vitest for testing).\n\n5. **Test Coverage**: Comprehensive tests are in place covering:\n   - Full-text search with ranking\n   - Snippet highlighting with `<mark>` tags\n   - Phrase queries with quotes\n   - Pagination\n   - Autocomplete suggestions\n   - FTS synchronization on CRUD operations\n   - Special character handling\n   - Performance benchmarks"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a682f415ab8e8b6af (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 37888\ntool_uses: 12\nduration_ms: 35303</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"bca8a425-df34-48ca-95ff-1b2f4f2672a4","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:56:25.381Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /workspace. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory structure\n2. Contents of all source files: src/db.ts, src/models.ts, src/routes.ts, src/errors.ts, src/server.ts, src/seed.ts\n3. Contents of test files: tests/notes.test.ts, tests/search.test.ts\n4. package.json for dependencies and scripts\n\nRead ALL of these files completely and provide their full contents.","agentId":"a682f415ab8e8b6af","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a complete summary.\n\n## Codebase Exploration Summary\n\n### Directory Structure\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts\n│   ├── models.ts\n│   ├── routes.ts\n│   ├── errors.ts\n│   ├── server.ts\n│   └── seed.ts\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts\n│   └── search.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n├── .gitignore\n├── TASK.md\n└── [git and other config files]\n```\n\n---\n\n### File Contents\n\n#### `/workspace/package.json`\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/src/db.ts`\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createDatabase(path?: string): Database.Database {\n  const db = path ? new Database(path) : new Database(':memory:');\n\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  // Create notes table\n  db.exec(`\n    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n      id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n      title TEXT NOT NULL,\n      body TEXT NOT NULL,\n      tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n      created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n      updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n    )\n  `);\n\n  return db;\n}\n\nexport function seedDatabase(db: Database.Database): void {\n  const insert = db.prepare(`\n    INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n  `);\n\n  const notes = getSeedNotes();\n\n  const insertMany = db.transaction((items: { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[]) => {\n    for (const item of items) {\n      insert.run(item.title, item.body, item.tags);\n    }\n  });\n\n  insertMany(notes);\n}\n\nfunction getSeedNotes(): { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[] {\n  return [\n    {\n      title: 'Getting Started with TypeScript',\n      body: 'TypeScript is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript. It adds optional static typing and class-based object-oriented programming to the language. TypeScript is designed for development of large applications and transcompiles to JavaScript.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'typescript', 'javascript']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Introduction to Python Programming',\n      body: 'Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language known for its simplicity and readability. It supports multiple programming paradigms including procedural, object-oriented, and functional programming. Python is widely used in web development, data science, and automation.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'python']),\n    },\n    // ... [45 more seed notes covering topics like databases, cooking, travel, science, music, health, etc.]\n    {\n      title: 'Fermentation and Pickling',\n      body: 'Fermentation preserves food using beneficial bacteria. Sauerkraut, kimchi, kombucha, and yogurt are popular fermented foods. Basic lacto-fermentation needs only vegetables, salt, and water. Maintain proper salt ratios (2-3%), keep vegetables submerged, and ferment at room temperature for optimal results.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'fermentation', 'preservation']),\n    },\n  ];\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/src/models.ts`\n```typescript\nexport interface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;\n  rank: number;\n}\n\nexport interface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/src/routes.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { Note, NoteInput } from './models.js';\nimport { NotFoundError, ValidationError } from './errors.js';\n\nexport function createRoutes(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // GET /notes - List all notes (with optional tag filter)\n  router.get('/notes', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const tag = req.query.tag as string | undefined;\n\n      let notes: Note[];\n      if (tag) {\n        // Use a join with json_each for tag filtering\n        const tagStmt = db.prepare(`\n          SELECT DISTINCT notes.* FROM notes, json_each(notes.tags)\n          WHERE json_each.value = ?\n          ORDER BY created_at DESC\n        `);\n        notes = tagStmt.all(tag) as Note[];\n      } else {\n        const stmt = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes ORDER BY created_at DESC');\n        notes = stmt.all() as Note[];\n      }\n\n      res.json({ notes });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // GET /notes/:id - Get single note\n  router.get('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const stmt = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?');\n      const note = stmt.get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!note) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      res.json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // POST /notes - Create note\n  router.post('/notes', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const input = req.body as NoteInput;\n\n      if (!input.title || input.title.trim() === '') {\n        throw new ValidationError('Title is required');\n      }\n      if (!input.body || input.body.trim() === '') {\n        throw new ValidationError('Body is required');\n      }\n\n      const tags = input.tags ? JSON.stringify(input.tags) : '[]';\n      const stmt = db.prepare(`\n        INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n      `);\n      const result = stmt.run(input.title, input.body, tags);\n\n      const note = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(result.lastInsertRowid) as Note;\n      res.status(201).json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // PUT /notes/:id - Update note\n  router.put('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const existing = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!existing) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      const input = req.body as Partial<NoteInput>;\n      const title = input.title ?? existing.title;\n      const body = input.body ?? existing.body;\n      const tags = input.tags ? JSON.stringify(input.tags) : existing.tags;\n\n      const stmt = db.prepare(`\n        UPDATE notes SET title = ?, body = ?, tags = ?, updated_at = datetime('now')\n        WHERE id = ?\n      `);\n      stmt.run(title, body, tags, id);\n\n      const note = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note;\n      res.json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // DELETE /notes/:id - Delete note\n  router.delete('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const existing = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!existing) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      db.prepare('DELETE FROM notes WHERE id = ?').run(id);\n      res.status(204).send();\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/src/errors.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\n\nexport class NotFoundError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 404;\n  constructor(message = 'Resource not found') {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'NotFoundError';\n  }\n}\n\nexport class ValidationError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 400;\n  constructor(message = 'Validation failed') {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'ValidationError';\n  }\n}\n\nexport function errorHandler(\n  err: Error,\n  _req: Request,\n  res: Response,\n  _next: NextFunction\n): void {\n  if (err instanceof NotFoundError) {\n    res.status(err.statusCode).json({ error: err.message });\n  } else if (err instanceof ValidationError) {\n    res.status(err.statusCode).json({ error: err.message });\n  } else {\n    console.error(err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/src/server.ts`\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createDatabase, seedDatabase } from './db.js';\nimport { createRoutes } from './routes.js';\nimport { errorHandler } from './errors.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface App {\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): App {\n  const db = createDatabase(dbPath);\n  const app = express();\n\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const routes = createRoutes(db);\n  app.use(routes);\n\n  app.use(errorHandler);\n\n  return { app, db };\n}\n\nexport function createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App {\n  const { app, db } = createApp(dbPath);\n  seedDatabase(db);\n  return { app, db };\n}\n\n// Start server if run directly\nconst isMain = process.argv[1]?.endsWith('server.js') || process.argv[1]?.endsWith('server.ts');\nif (isMain) {\n  const { app } = createSeededApp();\n  const port = process.env.PORT || 3000;\n  app.listen(port, () => {\n    console.log(`Server running on port ${port}`);\n  });\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/src/seed.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { createDatabase, seedDatabase } from './db.js';\n\nconst dbPath = process.env.DATABASE || 'notes.db';\nconsole.log(`Seeding database at: ${dbPath}`);\n\nconst db = createDatabase(dbPath);\nseedDatabase(db);\n\nconst count = (db.prepare('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM notes').get() as { count: number }).count;\nconsole.log(`Seeded ${count} notes successfully.`);\n\ndb.close();\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/tests/notes.test.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../src/server.js';\nimport t